gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString:
Each yearly PSLMP report (July 2003 to June 2011) includes an overview / discussion of the data for the year, as well as plots (for 12 stations) for monthly values and annual values. Data plots include mean monthly sea level, sea level anomolies, barometric pressure anomolies, air temperature anomolies, water temperature anomolies, and sea level trends.
Sea level values are relative to Tide Gauge Zero.
Data Parameter definitions (Source: http://www.bom.gov.au/oceanography/projects/spslcmp/data/data.shtml  ) are :
*********************************************
Sea Level : Observed sea levels are in metres above Tide Gauge Zero;
Water Temperature : Water Temperatures are in degrees Celsius (e.g. 20.5 deg C);
Air Temperature : Air Temperatures are in degrees Celsius (e.g. 20.5 deg C);
Barometric Pressure : Barometric Pressures are in hPa (mb) (e.g. 1010.1 hPa);
*********************************************
About the PSLMP: http://www.bom.gov.au/pacific/projects/pslm/index.shtml

These "PSLMP yearly reports" ceased after June 2011. 

Bureau Product ID(s) : IDO60102

Each data file includes hourly values, for all data variables, from a single station, for a single year. Data is updated monthly (to the file for the latest year), with a 1 month delay (e.g. Hourly values for the latest month are added approximately 1 month after the end of that month.)

Data Params definitions
 ( Source: http://www.bom.gov.au/oceanography/projects/spslcmp/data/data.shtml      ) are :
*********************************************
Sea Level : Observed sea levels are in metres above Tide Gauge Zero (e.g. 1.205 metres);
SSBM : Height of Seaframe Sensor Bench Mark above Tide Gauge Zero. Geoscience Australia has Survey Information [ftp://ftp.ga.gov.au/geodesy-outgoing/gnss/pub/SPSLCMP/ ] for the benchmarks near the tide gauges. SSBM is NOT changed to agree with this survey information, unless there is a known shift in SSBM;
Water Temperature : Water Temperatures are in degrees Celsius (e.g. 20.5 deg C);
Air Temperature : Air Temperatures are in degrees Celsius (e.g. 20.5 deg C);
Barometric Pressure : Barometric Pressures are in hPa (mb) (e.g.. 1010.1 hPa);
Residuals : Residual sea levels are in metres (e.g. -0.014m indicates that the observed sea level is 0.014m below predicted sea level);
Adjusted Residuals : Sea level anomalies are in metres (e.g. -0.077m indicates that the observed sea level is 0.077m below predicted sea level, adjusted for the static barometric pressure effect);
Wind Direction : Wind Directions in Degrees True (e.g. 205 degrees True). The wind direction is the average of the last six, one-minute wind direction measurements taken in the previous hour;
Wind Gust : Wind Gusts are in m/sec (e.g. 8.5 m/sec). The wind gust is the maximum of the sixty, one-minute wind gust measurements taken in the previous hour;
Wind Speed : Wind Speeds are in m/sec (e.g. 6.5 m/sec). The wind speed is the average of the last six, one-minute wind speed measurements taken in the previous hour;
*********************************************
About the PSLMP stations: http://www.bom.gov.au/oceanography/projects/spslcmp/data/data.shtml 

